<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Vector Intelligence — Campaign Planning</title>
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cormorant+Garamond:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Sans:wght@300;400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  *, *::before, *::after { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

:root {
–navy:   #0f1f3d;
–navy2:  #1a3260;
–gold:   #b8922a;
–gold2:  #d4aa44;
–cream:  #f5f1ea;
–text:   #1a1a1a;
–muted:  #5a5a5a;
–rule:   #d0c9bc;
}

html { font-size: 15px; }

body {
font-family: ‘DM Sans’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 300;
background: var(–cream);
color: var(–text);
min-height: 100vh;
}

/* ── HEADER ─────────────────────────────────────────── */
header {
background: var(–navy);
padding: 0;
position: relative;
overflow: hidden;
}

header::before {
content: ‘’;
position: absolute;
inset: 0;
background:
repeating-linear-gradient(
90deg,
transparent,
transparent 119px,
rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 119px,
rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 120px
),
repeating-linear-gradient(
0deg,
transparent,
transparent 59px,
rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 59px,
rgba(255,255,255,0.025) 60px
);
pointer-events: none;
}

.header-inner {
max-width: 900px;
margin: 0 auto;
padding: 56px 48px 48px;
position: relative;
z-index: 1;
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
gap: 32px;
align-items: end;
}

.logo-block { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }

.wordmark {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-weight: 700;
font-size: 2.8rem;
color: #fff;
letter-spacing: 0.06em;
line-height: 1;
}

.wordmark span {
color: var(–gold2);
}

.tagline {
font-size: 0.78rem;
font-weight: 400;
letter-spacing: 0.2em;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
}

.header-rule {
display: flex;
align-items: center;
gap: 12px;
padding-bottom: 4px;
}

.header-rule span {
display: block;
width: 48px;
height: 2px;
background: var(–gold);
}

.header-rule p {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-style: italic;
font-size: 1.05rem;
color: rgba(255,255,255,0.65);
white-space: nowrap;
}

/* ── GOLD BAR ───────────────────────────────────────── */
.gold-bar {
background: var(–gold);
height: 4px;
}

/* ── MAIN ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
main {
max-width: 900px;
margin: 0 auto;
padding: 56px 48px 64px;
}

/* ── INTRO ──────────────────────────────────────────── */
.intro {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
gap: 48px;
padding-bottom: 52px;
border-bottom: 1px solid var(–rule);
margin-bottom: 52px;
}

.intro-headline {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-size: 2.1rem;
font-weight: 600;
line-height: 1.25;
color: var(–navy);
}

.intro-headline em {
font-style: italic;
color: var(–gold);
}

.intro-body {
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
justify-content: center;
gap: 14px;
}

.intro-body p {
font-size: 0.93rem;
line-height: 1.75;
color: var(–muted);
}

.intro-body p strong {
color: var(–text);
font-weight: 500;
}

/* ── WHAT WE DO ─────────────────────────────────────── */
.section-label {
font-size: 0.68rem;
letter-spacing: 0.22em;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–gold);
font-weight: 500;
margin-bottom: 28px;
display: flex;
align-items: center;
gap: 10px;
}

.section-label::after {
content: ‘’;
display: block;
flex: 1;
height: 1px;
background: var(–rule);
}

.capabilities {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
gap: 2px;
margin-bottom: 52px;
border: 1px solid var(–rule);
}

.cap-item {
background: #fff;
padding: 28px 24px;
position: relative;
}

.cap-item::before {
content: ‘’;
display: block;
width: 24px;
height: 3px;
background: var(–gold);
margin-bottom: 16px;
}

.cap-title {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-size: 1.1rem;
font-weight: 600;
color: var(–navy);
margin-bottom: 10px;
line-height: 1.3;
}

.cap-desc {
font-size: 0.82rem;
line-height: 1.7;
color: var(–muted);
}

/* ── DIFFERENTIATORS ────────────────────────────────── */
.diff-grid {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
gap: 32px;
margin-bottom: 52px;
padding-bottom: 52px;
border-bottom: 1px solid var(–rule);
}

.diff-item {
display: flex;
gap: 16px;
align-items: flex-start;
}

.diff-number {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-size: 2rem;
font-weight: 700;
color: var(–gold);
line-height: 1;
min-width: 32px;
opacity: 0.6;
}

.diff-text h4 {
font-size: 0.85rem;
font-weight: 500;
color: var(–navy);
margin-bottom: 6px;
letter-spacing: 0.02em;
}

.diff-text p {
font-size: 0.8rem;
line-height: 1.7;
color: var(–muted);
}

/* ── HOW IT WORKS ───────────────────────────────────── */
.how-grid {
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
gap: 0;
margin-bottom: 52px;
position: relative;
}

.how-grid::before {
content: ‘’;
position: absolute;
top: 22px;
left: calc(12.5% + 12px);
right: calc(12.5% + 12px);
height: 1px;
background: var(–rule);
z-index: 0;
}

.how-step {
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
align-items: center;
text-align: center;
padding: 0 12px;
position: relative;
z-index: 1;
}

.step-dot {
width: 44px;
height: 44px;
border-radius: 50%;
background: var(–navy);
border: 2px solid var(–navy);
display: flex;
align-items: center;
justify-content: center;
margin-bottom: 14px;
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-size: 1.05rem;
font-weight: 700;
color: var(–gold2);
}

.step-title {
font-size: 0.8rem;
font-weight: 500;
color: var(–navy);
margin-bottom: 6px;
line-height: 1.3;
}

.step-desc {
font-size: 0.75rem;
line-height: 1.65;
color: var(–muted);
}

/* ── FOOTER CTA ─────────────────────────────────────── */
.cta-block {
background: var(–navy);
padding: 40px 48px;
display: grid;
grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
gap: 32px;
align-items: center;
margin: 0 -48px -64px;
}

.cta-block h3 {
font-family: ‘Cormorant Garamond’, serif;
font-size: 1.5rem;
font-weight: 600;
color: #fff;
line-height: 1.3;
margin-bottom: 6px;
}

.cta-block p {
font-size: 0.82rem;
color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
line-height: 1.6;
}

.cta-contact {
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
align-items: flex-end;
gap: 6px;
flex-shrink: 0;
}

.cta-email {
font-size: 0.88rem;
font-weight: 500;
color: var(–gold2);
letter-spacing: 0.02em;
text-decoration: none;
border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212,170,68,0.3);
padding-bottom: 2px;
}

.cta-note {
font-size: 0.72rem;
color: rgba(255,255,255,0.3);
letter-spacing: 0.08em;
text-transform: uppercase;
}

/* ── PRINT STYLES ───────────────────────────────────── */
@media print {
body { background: white; }
.cap-item { background: #f9f9f9; }
}

@media (max-width: 720px) {
.header-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
.intro { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
.capabilities { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
.diff-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
.how-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; }
.how-grid::before { display: none; }
.cta-block { grid-template-columns: 1fr; margin: 0 -24px -64px; padding: 32px 24px; }
.cta-contact { align-items: flex-start; }
main { padding: 40px 24px 64px; }
.header-inner { padding: 40px 24px 36px; }
}
</style>

</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="header-inner">
    <div class="logo-block">
      <div class="wordmark">VECTOR<span>.</span></div>
      <div class="tagline">Campaign Intelligence &nbsp;·&nbsp; All Levels of Government</div>
    </div>
    <div class="header-rule">
      <span></span>
      <p>Know your path. Close the gap.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="gold-bar"></div>

<main>

  <!-- INTRO -->

  <section class="intro">
    <h2 class="intro-headline">
      Every campaign has a number.<br>
      <em>Vector finds it —<br>and shows you how to reach it.</em>
    </h2>
    <div class="intro-body">
      <p>Vector Intelligence is a <strong>managed campaign analytics service</strong> built for candidates and campaign professionals who need more than a gut feeling about whether their field plan is going to work.</p>
      <p>We don't sell software licenses. We embed a senior analyst in your campaign for the cycle — running the numbers, managing the model, and delivering answers on your schedule, every week through election day.</p>
      <p>From city council to U.S. Senate, the core question is always the same: <strong>how many votes do you need, and do you have a realistic path to get them?</strong> That's what Vector was built to answer.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CAPABILITIES -->

  <div class="section-label">What Vector Does</div>
  <div class="capabilities">

```
<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Win Path Modeling</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">We translate your universe, vote shares, and turnout assumptions into a precise picture of how many votes you need to win — and how far you are from that threshold today.</p>
</div>

<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Field Plan Feasibility</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">Your plan looks good on paper. Vector stress-tests it. We model your actual capacity — organizers, hours, contact rates, channel mix — against what the race actually requires.</p>
</div>

<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Persuasion & GOTV Modeling</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">We separate the work you can do from the votes it actually produces. Persuasion, turnout lift, and undecided allocation modeled together so your plan reflects reality.</p>
</div>

<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Budget & ROI Optimization</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">Which tactic closes the gap most efficiently? We compute cost per net vote across every tactic and optimize your mix under real budget and timeline constraints.</p>
</div>

<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Risk & Scenario Analysis</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">Monte Carlo simulation stress-tests your assumptions across 10,000 scenarios. You see your win probability range, not just a point estimate — and what it takes to move that number.</p>
</div>

<div class="cap-item">
  <div class="cap-title">Weekly Pacing & Reality Checks</div>
  <p class="cap-desc">As your field program runs, we compare actual contact rates and productivity to your assumptions. If the plan is drifting, you'll know — and you'll know exactly which lever to pull.</p>
</div>
```

  </div>

  <!-- DIFFERENTIATORS -->

  <div class="section-label">Why Vector</div>
  <div class="diff-grid">

```
<div class="diff-item">
  <div class="diff-number">01</div>
  <div class="diff-text">
    <h4>Managed, Not Self-Serve</h4>
    <p>You don't learn a tool. You get answers. We run the platform, manage the model, and deliver outputs — so your team stays focused on the campaign, not the software.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="diff-item">
  <div class="diff-number">02</div>
  <div class="diff-text">
    <h4>Deterministic by Design</h4>
    <p>Same inputs always produce the same outputs. No black boxes. Every number traces back to an assumption, and every assumption can be challenged and changed.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="diff-item">
  <div class="diff-number">03</div>
  <div class="diff-text">
    <h4>Voter File Integration</h4>
    <p>We integrate your voter file directly into the model — so universe construction, turnout baselines, and persuadable targeting are grounded in your actual data, not generic assumptions.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="diff-item">
  <div class="diff-number">04</div>
  <div class="diff-text">
    <h4>Standing Access, Full Cycle</h4>
    <p>Weekly reporting, 1–2 standing meetings per week, and on-call access to your analyst throughout the cycle. When race conditions shift, we turn around new scenarios same day.</p>
  </div>
</div>
```

  </div>

  <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->

  <div class="section-label">How an Engagement Works</div>
  <div class="how-grid">
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="step-dot">1</div>
      <div class="step-title">Initial Consultation</div>
      <p class="step-desc">We scope the race, assess data availability, and align on your cycle timeline and reporting cadence.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="step-dot">2</div>
      <div class="step-title">Model Build & Data Integration</div>
      <p class="step-desc">We build your win path model, integrate your voter file, and construct the opening scenario library.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="step-dot">3</div>
      <div class="step-title">Weekly Cycle Operations</div>
      <p class="step-desc">Standing meetings, weekly scenario outputs, field pacing reports, and on-call access as the race evolves.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-step">
      <div class="step-dot">4</div>
      <div class="step-title">Election Day & Close</div>
      <p class="step-desc">War room scenario support through election day, followed by post-cycle archive and debrief.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->

  <div class="cta-block">
    <div>
      <h3>Ready to know your number?</h3>
      <p>Engagements are available for all levels of government. Initial consultations are complimentary.<br>Pricing is scoped to your race after the first conversation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cta-contact">
      <a href="mailto:contact@vectorintelligence.com" class="cta-email">contact@vectorintelligence.com</a>
      <span class="cta-note">Confidential &nbsp;·&nbsp; Not for distribution</span>
    </div>
  </div>

</main>
</body>
</html>
